---
# Enables WarningsAsErrors for src/ (production code) only. The root
# .clang-tidy keeps WarningsAsErrors: '' as the default (applies to tests/
# and everything else) because a project-wide scan on 2026-07-16 found 276
# pre-existing warnings under tests/ - most structural to the Google
# Benchmark macro API (BM_ naming convention, globals the BENCHMARK() macro
# itself generates) rather than fixable in test code. src/ was cleaned to
# zero warnings the same session (see docs/handoff/RESUME_HERE.md sec.3.4),
# so it can safely gate on warnings-as-errors; tests/ stays warn-only until
# that backlog is triaged separately.
InheritParentConfig: true
WarningsAsErrors: '*'
